Reasoning: The paper investigates strategies to improve the performance of search engines in response to exploratory medical queries, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of search engine results on the behavior of health searchers, which relates to human-computer interaction (HCI) and cyberpsychology (cs.CY). Additionally, the study involves analyzing large-scale data sets, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper touches upon the topic of health informatics (cs.HC) by investigating the real-world health-seeking behavior of searchers.
